column1: #Text=MH : In the third episode , the photographer who was the guest judge that week made a comment that he wanted to take you " to get something to eat , " and then criticized fellow contestant Natalie for being " a bit big " for modeling .
#Text=Did you feel you had the worst criticism , or do you think it was evenly spread out among all the girls ?
#Text=AM :
#Text=It was evenly spread out .
#Text=The criticism affected me as much as the others , but because I had a severe eating disorder at this time , I was very afraid of being exploited because of it .
#Text=MH : Right , you had some big concerns .
#Text=Ylenia also had self-image concerns while on the show , but we do n't know of her full story .
#Text=Do you still keep in contact with her , and if so , is she in a better state of mind now ?
#Text=AM : I 've talked to Ylenia maybe once since CNTM and personally I do not know how she is handling herself .
#Text=MH : Tricia Helfer hired a personal trainer for an episode , and he told you to revise your diet and to gain weight in your backside and in your thighs .
#Text=Were you afraid to listen to him or did you mentally process his tips but were hesitant anyway ?
#Text=AM : I knew out of every guest on the show that he was the most sincere in his advice .
#Text=I wanted to do what he said , but I knew that it was just for the show and therefore did n't abide .
#Text=I have talked to him recently and shared my story and he is so supportive of the way I look now and my true success story .
#Text=MH :
#Text=He was also the same guest who memorably destroyed a scale with a sledgehammer .
#Text=Since Tricia Helfer invited him , do you feel that she was sincere about wanting all the contestants to be healthy ?
#Text=Did she know you had an eating disorder ?
#Text=AM : Tricia Helfer knows the demands of the industry as she lives them herself .
#Text=She was not the producer of the show and did not plan the show , so I assume she is doing as she is told , knowing full well that weight was a big issue amongst all of us .
#Text=They all knew that I had an eating disorder as I barely ate on that show .
#Text=If anyone did not know , they were just plain naive .
